intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to: 
Articulate the key computing science challenges posed by many core architectures, the technologies available to address them, and the challenges of building reliable and scalable systems;
Design and implement simple parallel applications on shared and distributed memory architectures;
Evaluate the scaling properties of simple parallel applications;
Design and implement simple reliable distributed applications, selecting appropriately from various families of algorithm used in distributed systems, based on specific system requirements;
Evaluate the reliability properties of simple distributed applications.
